r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> talked ye=
sterday</a> about the somewhat strange=C2=A0possibility that public investo=
rs might be=C2=A0<em>too=C2=A0</em>focused on the long term. At a conferenc=
e in Saudi Arabia, Blackstone Group=E2=80=99s Steve Schwarzman and=C2=A0Bla=
ckRock Inc.=E2=80=99s Larry Fink both suggested that oil prices are high be=
cause investors have become so jazzed about funding a future transition to =
green energy that they are no longer willing to fund oil drilling. I wrote:=
</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way to tell that story is =
that, influenced by Fink and others, investors now insist on long-term sust=
ainability. They believe that a zero-carbon world is coming, they want to i=
nvest in companies that will make money in a zero-carbon world, and they th=
ink that a lot of marginal oil drillers will not survive in that world. The=
 oil drillers might agree! =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re gonna drill for oil for 1=
0 years, sell it at $85 a barrel, make a lot of money for our investors, an=
d then close up shop when the world moves off oil=E2=80=9D is a perfectly r=
easonable business plan. But =E2=80=94 Schwarzman says =E2=80=94 investors =
will not finance it anymore, because they are myopically obsessed with the =
long run.[1]</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I also proposed s=
ome reasons that public-market investors might dislike=C2=A0businesses with=
 good short-term cash flows but poor long-term prospects:</p><blockquote><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The reason might be along the lines of =E2=80=9C=
public markets systematically undervalue the short-term cash flows of dying=
 businesses,=E2=80=9D or else =E2=80=9Cpublic-market investors require, or =
at least allow, corporate executives to do a big song and dance about inves=
ting for the long run and pivoting to some sustainable business model, so t=
hey won=E2=80=99t let a dying business just pay out its cash to shareholder=
s and die with dignity, but will instead demand that it squander that cash =
on doomed efforts to survive.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">I should emphasize: All this stuff is=C2=A0weird stuff. We have ju=
st come off a period of several years in which people went around constantl=
y complaining that public markets are too focused on the short term, that t=
hey undervalue long-term investment, that they care only about next quarter=
=E2=80=99s earnings. But I do think that we are in a different world now, o=
ne where public investors seem a bit <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/25498985.267682/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDYtMjgvaW52ZXN0b3JzLXdpbGwtYnV5LWFueXRoaW5nLW5vdz9=
jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDI4MjFfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bm=
V3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMTEwMjgmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cBccf9b706" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> less interested in capital discipline</a=
> and a bit more interested in the far future.[2]</p><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">A lot of this is captured by the term =E2=80=9CESG.=E2=80=9D Lots of=
 investors now care about environmental, social and governance factors; the=
y consider those factors alongside more traditional financial metrics like =
how much money a company made last quarter. Part of the appeal of ESG is th=
at ultimate investors =E2=80=94=C2=A0the big asset managers=E2=80=99 custom=
ers =E2=80=94=C2=A0want to save the planet and so will pay a premium for ES=
G investments. But another part of the appeal =E2=80=94=C2=A0and the part t=
hat big asset managers <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/25498985.267682/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbG=
VzLzIwMjEtMDctMTMvZWxvbi1tdXNrLW5ldmVyLXdhbnRlZC10by1iZS10ZXNsYS1jZW8_Y21wa=
WQ9QkJEMTAyODIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3Ns=
ZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMDI4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b85=
