</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If some random guy on Twitter with a b=
unch of numbers in his user name tweets that you should buy a stock=C2=A0th=
at is trading at $0.0003 per share and hasn=E2=80=99t filed any financial r=
eports in years, should you do it? I dunno, maybe? Do you like gambling? Pr=
obably what will happen, if the guy has 70,000 Twitter followers who follow=
 him specifically for penny-stock pumps, is that the stock will go up to, s=
ay, $0.004, a 1,233% gain, and then it will go down to, say, $0.0002, all i=
n the space of a few days. So the trick is to buy it when it=E2=80=99s low =
and sell it when it=E2=80=99s high. I mean, that=E2=80=99s always the trick=
, isn=E2=80=99t it, but by pumping a defunct penny stock your Twitter frien=
d has=C2=A0<em>created </em>a new instance of this game. That stock was not=
 doing anything, there was no way to buy it low and sell it high, and now i=
t is doing something and you can take your chances.=C2=A0It=E2=80=99s a pur=
e zero-sum game; the people who get in and out at the right time will make =
money and they will make that money from the people who get in and out at t=
he wrong time; nobody is investing in a business or whatever. But maybe you=
 find the game fun? People seem to.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhi=
le of course your Twitter friend got in at the right time (before he starte=
d pumping the stock), and he=E2=80=99s probably getting out at the right ti=
me too (while you=E2=80=99re buying the stock that he=E2=80=99s pumping). H=
e will=C2=A0win this game that he started. Which lowers the odds that you w=
ill also win. But not to zero. Take a chance, why not, live a little. This =
is not investing advice. =C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=
=99s a Securities and Exchange Commission <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/25498985.267682/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3B=
yZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMS0yMTQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8fcef96a" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">enf=
orcement action</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securi=
ties and Exchange Commission [Tuesday] announced that it filed an emergency=
 action, and obtained an injunction and asset freeze, against Steven M. Gal=
lagher for allegedly committing securities fraud through a long running sch=
eme to manipulate stocks using Twitter.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The=
 SEC's complaint alleges that, since at least December 2019, Gallagher used=
 his Twitter handle, @AlexDelarge6553, to make thousands of tweets encourag=
ing his numerous followers to buy stocks in which Gallagher had secretly am=
assed holdings. As alleged, Gallagher would then sell those stocks at infla=
ted prices, while he continued to recommend others buy them =E2=80=94never =
disclosing that he was selling the stocks.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
"The complaint alleges that Gallagher used his followers for his own financ=
ial gain, tweeting out false advice to pump up the price of stocks he owned=
, so he could sell for a profit," said Richard Best, Director of the SEC's =
New York Regional Office. "This case is a reminder that investors should be=
 wary of taking financial advice from unverified sources on Twitter and oth=
er social media platforms."</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I =
mean, of course he did. Of course they should. My general assumption with p=
umps like these is that almost everyone is knowingly playing the game: Nobo=
dy who follows @AlexDelarge6553 for penny-stock recommendations thinks that=
 the stocks he recommends will go up=C2=A0<em>because the company has a cur=
e for cancer</em>; they think (correctly) that the stocks will go up becaus=
e he is pumping them, and they think (maybe correctly, maybe not) that they=
 will be able to get out before the stocks go down again. The <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25498985.267682/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMS9jb21wLXByMjAyMS0yMTQucGRm/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfc6acc84" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">SEC complaint</a>=C2=A0quotes som=
e tweets from the=C2=A0victims, and nobody is discussing the fundamentals:<=
/p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gallagher=E2=80=99s buy recomme=
ndations were clearly material, as evidenced, by way of example, by the ent=
husiastic responses to his recommendation from his followers, such as: (1) =
=E2=80=9CI downloaded ameritrade just to follow your moves but don=E2=80=99=
t have access to my funds until Friday morning=E2=80=A6..the hurt of not be=
ing able to make moves=E2=80=9D; (2) =E2=80=9C#buyscie stick to the plan=E2=
=80=9D; (3) =E2=80=9CActually was just running that through my head. It can=
t go down=E2=80=9D; (4) =E2=80=9C#buyscie I really hope this works=E2=80=9D=
; (5) =E2=80=9CYOU ARE THE MAN! BRILLIANT=E2=80=9D; (6) =E2=80=9CI m dancin=
g boss =EF=81=8A=E2=80=9D; (7) =E2=80=9CHow soon can we buy again?=E2=80=9D=
; (8) =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m with you #buyscie=E2=80=9D; (9) =E2=80=9CI have =
a feeling I=E2=80=99ll be loading more $SCIE in the morning.=E2=80=9D</p></=
blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That said, in that instance =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0a defunct company called SpectraScience Inc., ticker SCIE =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0@AlexDelarge6553 really did tweet that it had a cure for cancer! I=
 mean, he mostly tweeted about how he was going to pump SCIE, and then abou=
t how he was pumping SCIE, e.g.:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">Gallagher began his campaign of public SCIE touts, including tweeting =E2=
=80=9Ci loaded this $scie future alert i think,=E2=80=9D and, on December 8=
, =E2=80=9C$scie will have its day im loading these cheap levels. hint=E2=
=80=9D. ..</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gallagher issued a red Alert to =
buy SCIE, which said: =E2=80=9C$scie! Challenge buy Alert trips to pennies =
hold and we all win big!=E2=80=9D[4]</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">But he also tweeted this:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">SpectraScience, Inc. is focused on developing its WavSTAT Optical Biopsy =
System (WavSTAT). The WavSTAT employs a risk technology that optically illu=
minates tissue in real-time to distinguish between normal and pre cancerous=
 or cancerous tissue. $scie #buyscie; and</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">C=
ancer killing with patents. #buyscie.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">I feel like if you omitted the false claims about curing cancer you=
=E2=80=99d maybe get in less trouble with the SEC (still some trouble! not =
legal advice!), and it would work just about as well. Who could possibly be=
lieve you about the cancer?</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" borde=
